{{Infobox organization |name = Bangladesh Law Commission |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1996 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.lc.gov.bd/ Bangladesh Law Commission] |remarks = }} '''Bangladesh Law Commission''' is an independent body, set up through an act passed in the national parliament that reviews laws and recommends reforms when necessary in Bangladesh and is located in [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="mja">{{cite web|last1=Ahmed|first1=Naimuddin|title=Law Commission|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Law_Commission|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=28 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Law Commission is comatose|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-91464|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=28 October 2016|date=7 June 2009}}</ref> Former chief justice [[A. B. M. Khairul Haque]] is the present chairman of the commission.<ref>{{cite web|title=Law Commission chairman feels Bangladesh laws not used well|url=http://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2016/09/28/law-commission-chairman-feels-bangladesh-laws-not-used-well|website=bdnews24.com|accessdate=28 October 2016}}</ref>
==History== There has a number of temporary law commissions in the history of Bangladesh, the first one being set up in 1974. On 9 September 1996 the first permanent law commission was constituted. The first chairman of the commission was [[Fazle Kaderi Mohammad Abdul Munim]], a former chief justice of Bangladesh.<ref name="mja" /> In 2016 it drafted the Liberation War Denial Crimes Act, 2016 which made denying war crimes in the Bangladesh Liberation war a crime.<ref>{{cite web|title=Liberation War Denial Crimes Act drafted|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/backpage/liberation-war-denial-crimes-act-drafted-1198240|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=28 October 2016|date=23 March 2016}}</ref>
