{{other uses|Blackshirts (disambiguation)}}
{{no footnotes|date=October 2017}}

'''Blackshirts''' are members of the [[anti-religious]], [[atheist]] quasi-political organization [[Dravidar Kazhagam]] in [[Tamil Nadu]], founded by [[Periyar Ramasami|"Periyar" E V Ramasamy]]. The members wear black shirts to mock and protest the [[saffron]] vestments of [[Hindu]] religious leaders and [[sadhus]] as black is generally associated with death and bad-luck in contrast with saffron's auspicious association. This has its origins in  the banning of black flags as a protest tool in Tamil Nadu. To circumvent this ban, members wore black shirts. Black shirts and black flags were also seen as a symbol of anarchy in southern India especially in Tamil Nadu during the early 20th century.

